# Architecture Patterns

## Domain-Driven Design (DDD)

- **Bounded contexts**: Organize by business domain, not technical layers
- **Domain models**: Core business logic isolated from infrastructure
- **Ubiquitous language**: Use domain terminology consistently
- **Aggregate roots**: Clear boundaries for data consistency

## Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters)

- **Ports**: Interfaces defined in domain/application layers
- **Adapters**: Implementations in infrastructure layer
- **Dependency inversion**: High-level modules don't depend on low-level modules

## Modular Monolith → Microservices

- **Start modular**: Single deployable unit with clear internal boundaries
- **Extract services**: When scale/team size demands, extract modules to services
- **Module boundaries**: Each module has single responsibility, stable interfaces

## Event-Driven Architecture

- **Domain events**: Capture state changes as events
- **Event handlers**: React to events asynchronously
- **Decoupling**: Services communicate via events, not direct calls

## API Design

- **RESTful**: Use REST conventions (resources, HTTP methods, status codes)
- **Type safety**: Generate TypeScript types from OpenAPI schemas
- **Contract testing**: Ensure frontend/backend contracts match
- **Versioning**: Version APIs for backward compatibility

## Frontend/Backend Communication

- **API contract**: Define in OpenAPI/Swagger, generate types
- **Service layer**: Abstract API calls in frontend service layer
- **Error handling**: Centralized error handling in API client
- **Type-safe clients**: Use generated types for API calls
